        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 1:43PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 143 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles southwest of Absarokee, or 21 miles northwest of Red Lodge,
moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Roscoe and Luther.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
